cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.CE, cs.AI 

This paper presents a specialized environment for programming courses that guides and supports students during all phases of program development. The paper focuses on the use of Prolog in this environment, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of reference implementations, diagnostic facilities, test cases, visualization tools, and slicing techniques, which are all related to software engineering (cs.SE) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also mentions a marking system, which could be related to computer education (cs.CE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in terms of assessing student performance and providing feedback.
